					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12156737#post-4328509</guid>
				<title>Thoughts after reading</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12156737/scp-4406#post-4328509</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 12 Aug 2019 08:53:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>IsomorphicCoffeeMug</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5578133</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Glad to see there are other people with similar interests working on computer-based SCPs. This is very well written, avoiding most of the pitfalls of computer/digital virus-based SCP listings (namely that their writers as a rule have no idea how computers or viruses actually function in real life) Though one would imagine that anti-memetic properties would lead to the complete failure of any attempt to decompile or reverse engineer it&#8230; Maybe GHIDRA (<a href="https://ghidra-sre.org/">https://ghidra-sre.org/</a>), being from the NSA, has hidden anti-thaumaturgic obfuscation countermeasures?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
